events.name: Machine Learning Study Jam

venue.name: SDK Training Center
venue.address_1: Al-Naseem Traffic Lights - Al-Hmaydeh Complex the 3rd Floor.

events.description:
Hello Friends!

We‚Äôre super excited to bring Google's latest Machine Learning offering - ‚ÄòMachine Learning Crash Course (MLCC)‚Äô to Jordan. This course is intended for those who wish to learn about ML from a practical, applied perspective that will enable them to use machine learning within their everyday projects, and who wish to benefit from the power of TensorFlow wrapped in convenient higher-level abstractions. This is a great opportunity for professionals, entrepreneurs, and students to gain some practical experience in ML and TensorFlow.

This course will be suitable for you, if:
- You are a strong programmer
- Ideally, you are at least somewhat familiar with Python. You don't need to be an expert.
- Ideally, you know at least a little about linear algebra and calculus.

This course is not recommended for:
- Participants with extensive machine learning backgrounds.
- Participants looking to learn about the lower-level intricacies of raw TensorFlow.
Although the course does contain some basic TensorFlow exercises, most of the exercises focus on high-level Tensor APIs.
Participants seeking advanced topics in machine learning such as image conventional models and recurrent/sequential models.

The format of this course:
We will be walking you through MLCC, its modules, and basic ML concepts. Additionally, we will have you go through selected modules of the course, with a teaching assistant guiding you in course‚Äôs practical pieces/exercises and troubleshooting and pieces of the content where you are struggling. The course is open to all so you can complete the remaining modules as a self-study after the session.

Other requirements? Additionally, we‚Äôd need you to bring:
- Your laptop and charger. You will need this to go through the online course.
- Pen & paper (or any other preferable option if you plan to take notes)
A can-do attitude!

Interested?
- Register here: https://forms.gle/ipBCdWPGeeztjoVs9 by 20 April.

Selected attendees would be notified by 25 April. Filling up this form doesn‚Äôt guarantee a confirmation.

Thanks!

DevFests are community-led, developer events hosted by GDG chapters around the globe focused on community building and learning about Google‚Äôs technologies. Each DevFest is inspired by and uniquely tailored to the needs of the developer community and region that hosts it.

events.name: || Machine Learning Study Group || Day 5

venue.name: ZINC YU (Zain Innovation Campus, Yarmouk University)
venue.address_1: Prince Al Hussein Bin Abdullah II Complex, Yarmouk University, Irbid

events.description:
We decided to run the ML Study Group for students who were at python study group in order to walk with them all the way right to learn the best practices on Machine Learning on Cloud and with TensorFlow.

Machine Learning Study Group is a series of sessions where we learn together the fundamentals of ML and Deep Learning on GCP, using APIs and TensorFlow as well as learn more about models and how to build your own model in python.

This Study Jam is intended for those who wish to learn about ML from a practical, applied perspective that will enable you to use machine learning in your everyday projects and learn about the power of TensorFlow.

Main topics:
1- ML APIs on GCP
2- Algorithms
3- Sklearn and Keras
4- neural network
5- TensorFlow

we will go through:- GCP, algorithms, ML using python, sklearn, keras, computer vision (CNN), speech recognition, TensorFlow, neural network and more.

Our Local UX Design Thinking instructors with coordination with the local GDGs & Google DevRel will be conducting a 2-day hands-on user experience masterclass for early-stage startups in Jordan, focused on Design thinking. This is a free event.

In recent years, design and user-centered thinking have been embraced by business leaders‚Äìnot just as a way to do design, but as a way to create an effective product development strategy. By attending this class with your cross-functional team, you will learn basic user-centered design processes and how to apply them throughout your entire product development cycle.
